\c 4  
\p
\v 1 Moreover he \w made|strong="H6213"\w* an \w altar|strong="H4196"\w* of \w brass|strong="H5178"\w*, \w twenty|strong="H6242"\w* \w cubits|strong="H0520"\w* the \w length|strong="H0753"\w* thereof, and \w twenty|strong="H6242"\w* \w cubits|strong="H0520"\w* the \w breadth|strong="H7341"\w* thereof, and \w ten|strong="H6235"\w* \w cubits|strong="H0520"\w* the \w height|strong="H6967"\w* thereof.   
\p
\v 2 ¶ Also he \w made|strong="H6213"\w* a \w molten|strong="H3332"\w* \w sea|strong="H3220"\w* of \w ten|strong="H6235"\w* \w cubits|strong="H0520"\w* from \w brim|strong="H8193"\w* to \w brim|strong="H8193"\w*, \w round|strong="H5696"\w* in \w compass|strong="H5439"\w*, and \w five|strong="H2568"\w* \w cubits|strong="H0520"\w* the \w height|strong="H6967"\w* thereof; and a \w line|strong="H6957"\w* of \w thirty|strong="H7970"\w* \w cubits|strong="H0520"\w* did \w compass|strong="H5437"\w* it round \w about|strong="H5439"\w*.\f + \fr 4.2 \ft from…: Heb. from his brim to his brim\f*  
